OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1780251071
OL,3,CGruelling heat expected to give way to
OL,4,Ccooler temperatures and sporadic rain
OL,6,FHighs of 24C are expected in London on
OL,7,FSunday, with 19C in Birmingham, 17C in
OL,8,FAberdeen and 19C in Belfast.
OL,10,FMeanwhile, outbreaks of rain are
OL,11,Fexpected to be most frequent and
OL,12,Fheaviest in northern and western
OL,13,Fareas, while the east and southeast
OL,14,Fremain mostly clear.
OL,16,FOn Tuesday, England and Wales
OL,17,Fexperienced their hottest May days on
OL,18,Frecord as temperatures soared to 35.1C
OL,19,Fin Kew Gardens, west London, while
OL,20,F32.9C was measured at Cardiff's Bute
OL,21,FPark, the Met Office said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
