OL,3,CGruelling heat expected to give way to
OL,4,Ccooler temperatures and sporadic rain
OL,6,FOn Saturday evening, South East Water
OL,7,Fsaid drinking water supplies had been
OL,8,Frestored for 15,500 customers across
OL,9,FKent, including in the Whitstable and
OL,10,FHerne Bay areas, following issues with
OL,11,Fits network over the hot period.
OL,13,FIncident manager Steve Benton said:
OL,14,F"Whilst this is positive, we are
OL,15,Fconscious that today has been another
OL,16,Fhot day and demand has remained high.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1780251071
OL,3,CGruelling heat expected to give way to
OL,4,Ccooler temperatures and sporadic rain
OL,6,F"Although our network is continuing to
OL,7,Frecover, levels of drinking water in
OL,8,Four storage tanks are still low and we
OL,9,Fare asking customers to use water for
OL,10,Fessential purposes only ` drinking,
OL,11,Fcooking, and hygiene.
OL,13,F"We are continuing to use our tankers
OL,14,Fto support the network and aid
OL,15,Frecovery"
OL,17,FThe company added that it was working
OL,18,Fon restoring supply to some 500
OL,19,Fcustomers who had no water, while a
OL,20,Ffurther 3,600 had intermittent
OL,21,Fsupplies.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUwD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1780251071
OL,3,CGruelling heat expected to give way to
OL,4,Ccooler temperatures and sporadic rain
OL,6,FMr Benton said: "We are also aware
OL,7,Fthat some customers in the Wincheap
OL,8,Farea of Canterbury may have been
OL,9,Fexperiencing no water, which is due to
OL,10,Fa burst water main. This is currently
OL,11,Fbeing repaired.
OL,13,F"In addition, there are approximately
OL,14,F3,600 customers who may be
OL,15,Fexperiencing low pressure or an
OL,16,Fintermittent supply during the day in
OL,17,Fthe Coxheath, Loose, Headcorn, Ulcombe
OL,18,Fand Benenden and Wraik Hill areas.
OL,26,@nD@QOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1780251071
OL,3,CGruelling heat expected to give way to
OL,4,Ccooler temperatures and sporadic rain
OL,6,F"This means that water will go on and
OL,7,Foff throughout the day, with no water
OL,8,For low pressure at peak times,
OL,9,Fparticularly between 4pm and 7pm.
OL,11,F"We are sincerely sorry to customers
OL,12,Ffor disruption to their water supply
OL,13,Fand know how frustrating it is,
OL,14,Fespecially in hot weather."
OL,16,FThe company said it had given out a
OL,17,Fmillion litres of water at its bottled
OL,18,Fwater stations across Kent, and was
OL,19,Fworking to identify new locations for
OL,20,Fcollection points.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUvD@[O]
